# i18n Translation Workflow

## Rule: All Locales Together

When adding or translating UI text, **always update all supported locales in one task**. Never add a key to one locale and leave others missing or with placeholder values.

Supported locales are defined in `app/i18n/index.ts`. Keep all locale files structurally aligned.

## Locale Files

```
app/
  i18n/
    index.ts       ← locale list and config
    locales/
      en.ts
      tr.ts
      es.ts
```

New keys must be added to `en.ts`, `tr.ts`, and `es.ts` in the same commit.

## Translation Quality

- Provide actual translated strings — no machine-like literal phrasing.
- Use the target language's natural orthography and punctuation:
  - `tr`: use `ç, ğ, ı, İ, ö, ş, ü` — do not ASCII-normalize.
  - `es`: use `á, é, í, ó, ú, ñ` — do not ASCII-normalize.
- Follow casing conventions per language (e.g., sentence case vs. title case differ by locale).

## Usage in Components

Use Nuxt's `@nuxtjs/i18n` auto-imported `useI18n()`:

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const { t } = useI18n();
</script>

<template>
  <p>{{ t('campaign.emptyState') }}</p>
</template>
```

Never hardcode user-facing strings directly in templates or scripts — always go through `t()`.
